oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Cossitt Library and Custom House, Memphis, Tenn.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: View of Cossitt Library and the Custom House in Memphis, Tennessee. Shows surrounding streets with carriages and people.
The Cossitt Library was founded in 1888 as the Cossitt-Goodwin Institute. It was the first public library in Memphis. The original library building was constructed in 1893.
